{"title":"In the Drops: Trek CarBack Radar tail light, Lusso Paragon Signature bibshorts, Coros Dura headunit, Maap Alt_Road cap","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/trek-carback-radar-tail-light","date":1723200766000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/trek-carback-radar-tail-light\">In the Drops: Trek CarBack Radar tail light, Lusso Paragon Signature bibshorts, Coros Dura headunit, Maap Alt_Road cap</a></p>\n\n<p>Happy Friday, young and old. With the Olympic TT and Road Race done and dusted, the world’s best have stopped cycling in sort-of straight lines and are now cycling in lopsided circles on the track. So multi-talented are these iron-hewn lords and ladies of creation that the change of tack barely seems to have registered. I can’t be the only ignorant road-lubber who sits on the sofa desperately reminding myself of all the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/olympic-track-cycling-explained\">different rules of the various disciplines</a>, before referring to The Match Sprint as ‘the cat and mouse one’ anyway.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But let’s raise a bidon to this summer of sport, which has been more or less peak telly. A couched potato allotment for the ages. Wimbledon, Glastonbury, the Euros, the cricket, Coventry City reaching the FA Cup semi-final (a personal highlight for me, anyway), the Tour and now the Olympics have all illuminated our hollow lives and transformed our sofas into thrones of the screen. It’s a miracle I’ve managed to do any cycling at all.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Grand Tours are back in business with <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes\">the Tour de France Femme 2024</a> kicking off on the 12th August but if you’re not ready to say goodbye to the Olympics yet, Will Strickson has shared some of <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/z_w_photography/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">Zac Williams’</a> best photos from <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/mens-olympic-road-race-paris-2024-gallery\">the men’s Road Race</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/womens-olympic-road-race-paris-2024-gallery\">the women’s Road Race</a>. Ewan has ranked <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/ranking-olympic-gold-bikes\">the best gold bikes from Olympic champions</a> through the years while <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-news-2024-olympics-road-race\">Robyn’s Pro Log</a> recaps all the news from the Olympics and elsewhere.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In tech stuff, Cervélo has launched a tweaked version of its endurance bike <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cervelo-caledonia-5-2025\">the Caledonia-5</a>, Sam Challis has all the details on the new gravel <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/sram-red-xplr-axs\">Sram Red XPLR AXS 13-speed drivetrain</a> and the colossal 32mm internal rim width <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/zipp-303-xplr-wheels\">Zipp 303 XPLR gravel wheels</a> that have launched concurrently. Andy Turner is emerging – nervous and squinting – into the dazzling light of day after updating our <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-cycling-sunglasses\">2024 buyer’s guide for the best sunglasses</a>. His bonce should be ok if he falls over though, as he’s only gone and completed <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-aero-helmets\">the best aero road helmets buyer’s guide</a> too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And now, like Sky Brown plummeting to earth, let’s tumble into the drops.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Trek CarBack radar tail light</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-970x648.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-970x648.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-1140x762.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02000-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Have you ever wanted one dazzling bright red eye in the back of your head? No, me neither. But as I’ve advanced in years, my desire to be visible on the bike has increased commensurately. And that’s where Trek’s CarBack radar tail light throbs into life.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While pretty hefty in size – think a chunky version of a Wahoo Elemnt Bolt – the CarBack has a number of potentially life-saving features. The light syncs with your head unit or phone to warn you when a car is approaching. This is slightly more gamified on a mobile phone screen. On my Wahoo, it takes the form of a vertical strip at the side of the screen which beeps and flashes when a car comes within 240m.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-970x648.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-970x648.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-1140x762.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02007-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Trek says the light, which has multiple different flash and solid modes, can be seen up to 2km away, plus there are clear LED battery status lights running down the side. Who needs friends when your trusty robot assistant can provide reliable road safety without the drawbacks of conversation? </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy now from <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/gb/en_GB/carback/\" target=\"_blank\">Trek (£169.99)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/dimitris-katsanis-podcast\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast episode 111: Dimitris Katsanis makes the world’s fastest bikes</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes-predictions-2024\">Cyclist’s Tour de France Femmes predictions 2024</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/evita-muzic-interview\">Évita Muzic interview: ‘If I had to choose between the Olympics or the Tour de France, it would be the Tour de France’</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes\">Tour de France Femmes 2024: Route, start list, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Lusso Paragon Signature bib shorts</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-970x648.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-970x648.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-1140x762.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02015-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Cycling bib shorts can be one of life’s great pleasures or a particular form of misery. It seems relatively common for brands to produce decent enough bibs, but it’s another matter entirely to pull something special out of the bag. And that’s what Manchester-based producer Lusso has done with its limited-edition handmade Paragon Signature Bib Shorts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"580\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02029-970x580.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02029-970x580.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02029-300x179.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02029-768x459.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02029-1536x919.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02029-2048x1225.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02029-750x449.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02029-1140x682.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On this strict production run of just 100 pairs, Lusso has used micro-knitted Italian fabric and raw cutting to eradicate grippers and keep the super smooth fabric compressed to the skin. The chamois is from Elastic Interface who provide the padding for many big brands including Gobik, but I’m yet to test the 8-hour comfort rating to its upper limit. Though it won’t see anyone’s eyes but mine, each pair has a unique chamois colourway which is a nice little detail.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-970x648.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-970x648.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-1140x762.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02019-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I’m always keen to wear British kit when available, and it’s a pleasure when it’s thoroughly well-made. I rode the Mortirolo in these bad boys last month and my keister came through with flying colours – it was my legs that were the problem.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy now from <a href=\"https://www.lusso.bike/products/paragon-signature-bib-shorts-limited-edition\" target=\"_blank\">Lusso (£200) </a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Coros Dura head unit and heart rate monitor</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-970x648.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-970x648.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-1140x762.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC01992-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I could fill an entire weekly column with bike computer gripes but weirdly I’ve never been commissioned. Whether it’s feeble battery life, infuriating firmware updates, clunky syncing, or interminable map loading, these little rectangles that promise such convenience often let me down.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Coros, with many dogs in the running-watch fight, has recently entered the head unit scrap. The Dura claims a pretty wild 120-hour battery life that’s topped up by its solar panel. This converts two hours of sun lounging into one additional hour of power.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-970x648.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-970x648.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-1140x762.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC019977-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s got all the usual features you’d expect from a head unit including a proprietary app where, amongst other things, you can create new routes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The minimalist arm-mounted Coros Heart Rate Monitor syncs up with the Dura to complete the virtuous circle of data. Oddly enough it offers less battery life than the head unit, with 38 hours of continuous use possible. Rather than using sensor pads, like chest-worn monitors, four green LEDs beam into your veins to take readings.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-970x648.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-970x648.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-1140x762.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02012-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy now from <a href=\"https://uk.coros.com/dura\" target=\"_blank\">Coros (£249 and £69)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Maap Alt_Road Legionnaires Cap</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"589\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02047-970x589.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02047-970x589.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02047-300x182.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02047-768x466.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02047-1536x932.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02047-2048x1243.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02047-750x455.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02047-1140x692.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Some people are born sunburnt, others achieve sunburn, and some have sunburn thrust upon them. I think I inhabit all three categories. As my aversion to risk has shot sunward (see above), my inclination to look traditionally ‘cool’ has waned. Lachlan Morton can sleep easy because I’ve officially hung up my cool boots.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-970x648.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-970x648.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-768x513.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-1536x1026.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-2048x1368.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-750x501.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-1140x762.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/DSC02054-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Maap Alt_Road Legionnaires cap (in orange of course) is the ultimate companion for my fellow sun-fearing ghost riders out there. For those days when you’re cycling the Sahara Desert or Death Valley, the cap and its poppable neck shade panel will fit underneath a helmet, but mainly it’s good for off-bike wear. Maap has also placed a couple of handy poppers on the front of the neck shade panel so that you can protect your chin from the beastly sun too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It boasts factor 50+ UPF protection, some good ventilation and it’s made from 100% recycled polyester. The peak isn’t rigid either, so for the bikepackers out there – it packs away really small.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I wore it on the hottest day of Glastonbury this year and in a single two-hour period I had nine different strangers ask me for suncream. Beware: this hat will quickly come to define you.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Buy now from <a href=\"https://maap.cc/uk/products/alt_road-legionnaires-cap-mars\" target=\"_blank\">Maap (£45)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature</strong></em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Le Col Pro Bib Shorts II</h2>\n\n\n\n<h2>RRP £185, Sale Price £140, Your Price £112</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/LeCol_EOSS_0724_Week1_CyclistNewsletter_OPT2_3-pro-bibs.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/LeCol_EOSS_0724_Week1_CyclistNewsletter_OPT2_3-pro-bibs.jpg 2000w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/LeCol_EOSS_0724_Week1_CyclistNewsletter_OPT2_3-pro-bibs-300x169.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/LeCol_EOSS_0724_Week1_CyclistNewsletter_OPT2_3-pro-bibs-970x546.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/LeCol_EOSS_0724_Week1_CyclistNewsletter_OPT2_3-pro-bibs-768x432.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/LeCol_EOSS_0724_Week1_CyclistNewsletter_OPT2_3-pro-bibs-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/LeCol_EOSS_0724_Week1_CyclistNewsletter_OPT2_3-pro-bibs-750x422.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/LeCol_EOSS_0724_Week1_CyclistNewsletter_OPT2_3-pro-bibs-1140x641.jpg 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The Pro Bib Shorts II incorporates expert aerodynamic insight, pro team learnings and rigorous testing to bring you a high-performance short that maximises speed without sacrificing comfort.</p>\n\n\n\n<div>\n<div><a href=\"https://lecol.cc/products/pro-bib-shorts-ii?variant=39962077167679&amp;discount=AFF-CYCLIST-20&amp;source=aw&amp;sv1=affiliate&amp;sv_campaign_id=1306327&amp;awc=15692_1722848360_1f4520b88df359f61acfe802b5e2c98b&amp;utm_source=AWIN&amp;utm_medium=1306327-Cyclist&amp;utm_campaign=Linking+via+Landing+Pages\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>BUY THE LE COL PRO BIB SHORTS II</strong></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div></div>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature ends</strong></em></p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>What we’re into this week: The NTS Breakfast Show w/Flo</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"474\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/image-970x474.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/image-970x474.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/image-300x147.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/image-768x375.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/image-1536x750.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/image-750x366.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/image-1140x557.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/image.png 1890w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For the most part, I’m hanging on the every word of my colleagues in the office, but for those rare moments when I need to buzz out the background babble of tyre sealant and rim width chat (yep, it’s like the Chelsea hotel up in here) then there is nothing quite like the Dalston-based radio station NTS and its utterly sensational Monday to Wednesday (9-11 am) host Flo Dill.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I’ve been listening to the station for almost a decade and, to me at least, it has matured like a honking cheese. NTS stands for Nuts to Soup which will only really register with fans of The Simpsons out there. Basically, it’s a community-led not-for-profit station that plays advert-free music ‘selected by people, not algorithms’. Almost all of my playlisted music comes from Flo, who freewheels through genres and chats with an effortlessness that looks easy but is anything but.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sure, it might look a bit trendy, but it’s also incredibly accessible and free – though some, like myself, choose to make a monthly donation to their patron/membership scheme. Plus, there’s an occasional Tuesday feature called MOTH (Matters of the Heart) where despondent millennials post their relationship quandaries into the website chat and the friendly woke-leaning bear pit offers ‘advice’.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Listen to <a href=\"https://www.nts.live/shows/the-breakfast-show-flo\" target=\"_blank\">NTS</a> (FREE)</strong></li>\n</u